name: Car accident
description: A traffic incident resulting in damage or injury.

name: Human trafficking for prostitution
description: The illegal trade of humans for exploitation, particularly in the sex industry.

name: Murder
description: The unlawful killing of another person with intent.

name: Suspect
description: An individual suspected of being involved in a crime or incident.

name: Terrorist
description: An individual involved in acts of terror, often targeting civilians.

name: Terrorist attack
description: An act of violence aimed at causing terror, usually targeting civilians or symbols of power.

name: Burglary
description: Illegal entry into a building with intent to commit a crime.

name: Fraud
description: Wrongful or criminal deception intended to result in financial or personal gain.

name: Cybercrime
description: Criminal activities carried out by means of computers or the internet.

name: Arson
description: The criminal act of deliberately setting fire to property.

name: Domestic violence
description: Abuse or violence within a domestic setting.

name: Embezzlement
description: Theft or misappropriation of funds placed in one's trust.

name: Kidnapping
description: The unlawful act of taking someone away by force.

name: Drug trafficking
description: Illegal production, distribution, or sale of drugs.

name: Money laundering
description: The process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money.

name: Assault
description: A physical attack on another person.

name: Vandalism
description: Deliberate destruction or damage to property.

name: Theft
description: The act of stealing someone else's property.

name: Forgery
description: The act of creating a false document with the intent to deceive.

name: Robbery
description: The act of taking property unlawfully from a person by force.

name: Environmental Violation
description: Activities that harm the environment, such as illegal dumping or pollution.

name: Shoplifting
description: The act of stealing goods from a retail establishment.

name: Illegal Parking
description: Parking a vehicle in a restricted area or in a hazardous manner.

name: Bribery
description: Offering, giving, receiving, or soliciting something of value to influence an action.

name: Public Intoxication
description: Being visibly drunk or intoxicated in a public place.

name: Trespassing
description: Entering another person's property without permission.

name: Identity Fraud
description: Using another individual's identity for fraudulent purposes.

name: Extortion
description: Obtaining something through force or threats.

name: Illegal Dumping
description: The unauthorized disposal of waste materials.

name: Tax Evasion
description: The illegal act of not paying taxes owed.

name: Perjury
description: Lying under oath during legal proceedings.

name: Counterfeiting
description: The production of imitation money, goods, or documents with intent to deceive.

name: Public Disorder
description: Conduct that disrupts public order, such as rioting or disturbing the peace.

name: Corruption
description: Dishonest or fraudulent conduct by those in power, typically involving bribery.

name: Forgery
description: Creating or altering a document with the intent to defraud.

name: Resisting Arrest
description: Attempting to evade or resist being taken into custody by law enforcement.

name: Animal Cruelty
description: Intentionally causing harm or suffering to animals.

name: Stalking
description: Repeated and unwanted attention or harassment of another person.

name: Voter Fraud
description: Illegal interference with the process of an election.

name: Child Endangerment
description: Putting a child in a situation where their safety is at risk.

name: Obstruction of Justice
description: Interfering with the operations of law enforcement or judicial systems.

name: Unlawful Assembly
description: A gathering of people for illegal purposes or in violation of legal restrictions.
